7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Otter.ai and Podcastle share a solid foundation of core features including Speech To Text. Where Otter.ai pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Api Access and Real Time, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Podcastle uniquely offers Text To Speech and Voice Cloning and Noise Removal and Podcast Editing and Custom Voices, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Otter.ai holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Podcastle scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Otter.ai offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $8.33/mo, compared to Podcastle's starting price of $11.99/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Otter.ai's free tier and Podcastle's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
